# Deploy (user does not deploy)

The user **does not run deploys**. After any change that affects production:

1. **Supabase Edge Functions** — Deploy every function you touched (or its callers). From repo root, use the linked project ref in `supabase/.temp/linked-project.json` (currently `yyriamwvtvzlkumqrvpm`):

   ```bash
   supabase functions deploy <name> [<name> ...] --project-ref yyriamwvtvzlkumqrvpm
   ```

   Typical Arc / combined-plan stack: `arc-setup-chat`, `generate-combined-plan`, `create-goal-and-materialize-plan`.

2. **Frontend** — Netlify builds from `main`. **Commit** and **`git push origin main`** so the site picks up client changes.

Do not end a shipping task with “you should deploy”; run deploy and push yourself when credentials/network allow.
